  1. Overview & Quick Start


  This VMware virtual machine appliance represents a fully configured
  ]project-open[ server. This VMware is suitable for testing ]po[ and
  for production use in small organizations (< 20 active users).

  In order to run ]project-open[ in your organization, you'll need
  to follow the steps below. Basic system administration knowledge 
  should be sufficient to perform these steps. Please see the following 
  chapters for full explanations of each step.


  - Download and install VMware Server 2.0 and start the VMware.

  - Copy or move the folder "project-open-v34" into:
	Win32:	c:/Virtual Machines
	Linux:	/var/lib/vmware/Virtual Machines

  - In your VMware control center choose "Virtual Machine -> Add machine
    to Inventory"

  - Configure the virtual machine. You may increase the memory size
    and change the network adaptor to "Bridge" mode.

  - After starting the virtual machine please login to Linux as "root":
	Username: root
	Password: root

  - After logging in please click on the "]po[ @ Localhost" icon in the 
    VMware's desktop. Please don't worry if you should see
    "Service not avaliable". This just means that the ]po[ server is still
    starting up. This process may take up to 60 seconds.

  - Once you see the login screen of ]po[, please choose:
	Email: sysadmin@tigerpond.com
	Password: system

  - As the next step please follow the System Configuration Wizard to
    configure ]po[ for your particular business size and industry.
    Don't spend too much time, you can repeat this step later as many
    times as you want.

  - As the next step you probably want to make your VMware accessible
    to other computers in your local area network. Please see:
    http://www.project-open.org/documentation/install_vm

  - As a last you need to delete the "Tigerpond" demo data in the system
    before you can use ]po[ in production for your company.
    Please go to Admin -> Cleanup Demo Data -> "Nuke all demo data" and
    then "Nuke Demo Users". Please "recycle" the remaining ]po[ Admin 
    users, by changing their email address to yours (they are owners of
    system objects, so they can't be deleted).

  - Please see the "Rollout Plan" for a methodology to roll-out ]po[:
    http://www.project-open.org/documentation/tutorial_rollout_plan



