  5. Download VMware Server and Start the ]po[ Server


  We recommend you use VMware Server 2.x from VMware's web site at
  http://www.vmware.com/products/server/. As an alternative, you can 
  also use the VMware Player product.

  VMware Server is available at no licensing cost. However, it is not 
  open-source software, and you will need to register in order to obtain 
  a license key to run VMware Server.

  Once your VMware Server is running, just move the "project-open-v34"
  included in this installer into VMware's "C:\Virtual Machines" folder
  (or wherever you have chosen to keep your virtual machines) and use
  File -> Open -> Browse to open this VMware.

  Before starting the VMware, please check the VMware's Devices:

  - Memory:
    The minimum is 512 MB, which is OK for testing purposes.
    For production, please increase this value to 1024 MB or higher.

  - Ethernet:
    Should be set to Bridged mode. Only in this mode will your VMware
    be visible to the rest of your intranet.


  After starting the VMware you will see some messages, and after 1 to 2
  minutes you will see a login screen. The default login is:

	Username:	root
	Password:	root



  ______________________________________________________________________

  6. Configure the VMware's IP Address


  In order to be able to access the ]project-open[ server from your
  Intranet, you'll need to find out the IP address of the VMware.

  To find out the IP address, double-click the "]po[ @ Localhost" icon
  in the VMware's desktop. A browser window should open with the ]po[ 
  login page. 
  You should see on the left a section called "Default Logins" with 
  sample users, and on the right an Email / Password login component.

  In this page please scroll down. To the lower right you will find:

  - Browser URL:	http://192.168.0.101/

  - IP Address:		192.168.0.101 (sample value)

  - Total Memory:	512 MByte (sample value)

  Now open a Web browser on your computer or another computer and enter 
  http://192.168.0.101/ (sample value, as above). 
  You should now get the same page as from inside the VMware.


  Troubleshooting:

  If you don't see the IP Address as above, there are two possible causes:

  - Fixed IP Addresses:
    Is it possible that you don't have a DHCP server in your network
    and work with fixed IP addresses? If so, please go to the VMware menu
    System -> Administration -> Network and choose a fixed IP address
    for your VMware.

  - VMware network not in "Bridged" mode:
    Please make sure you have set your VMware's Ethernet port
    to "Bridged" mode. Only in bridged mode will you be able to
    see the ]project-open[ server from your intranet.


  ______________________________________________________________________

  7. Basic configuration of ]project-open[


  In order to configure the VMware, please login as:

	Email:		sysadmin@tigerpond.com
	Password:	system


  You will now see the System Configuration Wizard that guides
  you through the configuration of the ]project-open[ System.

  The main purpose of this wizard is to simplify the system by
  disabling unnecessary functionality.

  For a maximum configuration please choose the "Other / Everything,"
  "Complete / Full Installation" and "Three Hierarchical Levels"
  options at the bottom of each wizard page.

  Going back to the "Home" page after 1 to 2 minutes, you will see
  a fully configured ]po[ server with demo data.



